        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 7:09PM CDT by NWS Lake Charles LA</headline>
        <description>At 709 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Clifton, or 10 miles southwest of Lena, moving south at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Clifton, Lacamp, Leander, Sieper, and Simpson.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
